Building a Protected-Mode Program

    This example shows how to compile and link a simple protected-mode
    program, and how to export the DOS4GOPTIONS string from both a C and
    C++ compiled object, regardless of the calling convention used.
	
    This example consists of these files, in the EXAMPLES\HELLO directory:

    HELLO.C     32-bit code source.

    MAKEFILE    Polymake-configured makefile to build all the example
                executables using either Microsoft VC 4.x and/or Watcom.


